he English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":63,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":74,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":92,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":105,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs John Wickingham was born about 1495, in Euston, Suffolk, England. She married John Wichingham about 1512, in Euston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1495–":"umbes 1495–Surnud","1485–Male":"1485–Surnud","1512–1544":"1512–1544","1514–1563":"1514–1563","1495–Female":"1495–Surnud","1495":"1495","ABT 1512":"umbes 1512","1514":"1514","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1600":"1600","1544":"1544","1587":"1587","1563":"1563","1485":"1485","about 1495":"umbes 1495","1549":"1549","Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, England","Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, England","Of, Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1495–":"noin 1495–Kuollut","1485–Male":"1485–Kuollut","1512–1544":"1512–1544","1514–1563":"1514–1563","1495–Female":"1495–Kuollut","1495":"1495","ABT 1512":"noin 1512","1514":"1514","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1600":"1600","1544":"1544","1587":"1587","1563":"1563","1485":"1485","about 1495":"noin 1495","1549":"1549","Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, England","Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, England","Of, Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1495–":"environ 1495–Décédée","1485–Male":"1485–Décédé","1512–1544":"1512–1544","1514–1563":"1514–1563","1495–Female":"1495–Décédée","1495":"1495","ABT 1512":"environ 1512","1514":"1514","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1600":"1600","1544":"1544","1587":"1587","1563":"1563","1485":"1485","about 1495":"environ 1495","1549":"1549","Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, Angleterre","Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, Angleterre","Of, Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, Ang